    "Use billete for ticket in Spain; boleto is common in Latin America.",
    "A qué hora asks at what time."
  ],
  "sections": [
    {
      "id": "phrases",
      "title": "Station phrases",
      "kind": "cards",
      "items": [
        {
          "es": "Quisiera un billete a Madrid.",
          "en": "I would like a ticket to Madrid."
        },
        {
          "es": "¿A qué hora sale el tren?",
          "en": "What time does the train leave?"
        },
        {
          "es": "¿De qué andén sale?",
          "en": "Which platform does it leave from?"
        },
        {
          "es": "El tren sale a las cinco.",
          "en": "The train leaves at five."
        },
        {
          "es": "Necesito un billete de ida.",
          "en": "I need a one-way ticket."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "practice",
      "title": "Buying a ticket",
      "kind": "dialogue",
      "lines": [
        {
          "speaker": "A",
          "es": "Quisiera un billete a Madrid, por favor.",
          "en": "I would like a ticket to Madrid, please."
        },
        {
          "speaker": "B",
          "es": "¿De ida o de ida y vuelta?",
          "en": "One-way or round-trip?"
        },
        {
          "speaker": "A",
          "es": "De ida, por favor.",
          "en": "One-way, please."
        },
        {
          "speaker": "B",
          "es": "Sale a las cinco.",
          "en": "It leaves at five."
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
